- All SSPs: support PFC_SUPPORT_HEADER_SIGN for DCE/RPC
- Refactor SSPs and DCE/RPC client/server to use req_flags in GSS_Init_sec_context
- KerberosSSP:
  - support DCE_STYLE (for DCE/RPC)
  - add MIC/WRAP support
- NTLMSSP: fix SeqNum when used with SPNEGO
- Fix a bunch of SPNEGO edge cases
- Many tests

commit.message:
DNS: add HINFO resource record (#4299)

https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc1035#section-3.3.2

The patch was also cross-checked with Wireshark:
```
tdecode(Ether()/IP()/UDP()/DNS(raw(DNS(an=[DNSRRHINFO(rrname='H.local', os='OS', cpu='CPU')]))))
...
    Answers
        H.local: type HINFO, class IN, CPU CPU, OS OS
            Name: H.local
            Type: HINFO (host information) (13)
            Class: IN (0x0001)
            Time to live: 0 (0 seconds)
            Data length: 7
            CPU Length: 3
            CPU: CPU
            OS Length: 2
            OS: OS
```
